<p>I have base object called <code>IList</code>. Then I have <code>VectorList</code>, that inherits <code>IList</code>.</p>  <p>then I have function like this:</p>  <pre><code>std::unique_ptr&lt;IList&gt; factory(){     auto vlist = std::make_unique&lt;VectorList&gt;();     return vlist; } </code></pre>  <p>This compiles without problem under <code>gcc</code>, but <code>clang</code> gives following error:</p>  <pre><code>test_file.cc:26:9: error: no viable conversion from 'unique_ptr&lt;VectorList, default_delete&lt;VectorList&gt;&gt;' to       'unique_ptr&lt;IList, default_delete&lt;IList&gt;&gt;'         return vlist; </code></pre>  <p>How is proper way to handle this kind of errors? </p>